President Biden spoke at the Pennsylvania Convention Center in Philadelphia, addressing various topics including the recent attack on Nancy Pelosi's home, the state of the economy, healthcare, and the Republican agenda. He highlighted the progress made in the economy, such as job creation and lower gas prices. He also discussed his administration's efforts to lower healthcare costs, protect Social Security and Medicare, and reduce prescription drug prices. Biden criticized the Republican agenda, accusing them of wanting to cut social programs, eliminate the Affordable Care Act, and threaten the right to vote. He urged people to vote and emphasized the importance of unity in moving the country forward.